  "litigation-brief-f3-v-polo": {
    "kind": "markdown",
    "content": "# LEGAL CASE BRIEF: F3 Polo vs. Polo Enterprises (Janek Gazecki)\n**Subject:** Federal Court Case NSD2008/2019 & Current Litigation Strategy  \n**Date:** May 2026  \n**Confidentiality:** For Strategic Planning Only\n\n## 1. CORE DISPUTE SUMMARY\nThe Applicant, Polo Enterprises Holdings Pty Ltd (controlled by John “Janek” Gazecki), has alleged trademark infringement and damages exceeding $10 million. The Respondents (F3 Polo) maintain the claim is an “Abuse of Process” and “Lawfare” designed to eliminate market competition.\n\n## 2. KEY CONTRADICTIONS & DUTY OF CANDOUR BREACHES\nThe following points are critical for the June 5 Security for Costs hearing:\n\n### A. The McCabes Bankruptcy Denial\n- **The Sworn Statement:** On 12 Nov 2025, Gazecki told the Registrar there were “no costs orders... ever” that were unpaid.\n- **The Evidence:** Federal Court records (NSD2008/2019) show a Bankruptcy Notice was issued by McCabes Lawyers against Gazecki in May 2019. It took 3 years of litigation before it was set aside “by consent” in July 2022.\n- **Strategic Impact:** This proves a historical lack of candour to the Court and a pattern of being a “serial procedural litigant.”\n\n### B. The “Impecuniosity” vs. Maldives Vacation\n- **The Claim:** Gazecki has sworn affidavits claiming “total business collapse” and an inability to pay school fees or court-ordered security ($60,000).\n- **The Reality:** In April 2026, Gazecki and his wife (Natalie Decorte) traveled to the Park Hyatt Maldives.\n- **The Evidence:** Social media tagging and professional modeling/photo shoots confirm a luxury international production.\n- **Strategic Impact:** If the Director has access to funds/benefits for a $40k+ Maldives trip, the claim of impecuniosity is legally fraudulent.\n\n### C. The Manufactured “Horse Failure”\n- **The Affidavit Claim:** Gazecki swears his business will fail because he “cannot get horses” for the June 2026 Rockhampton event.\n- **The Evidence:** An email from Gazecki (Legal Watch Australia letterhead) to his 15-year supplier “JT” shows Gazecki setting a 48-hour deadline and effectively terminating the relationship himself based on “word on the street” gossip.\n- **Strategic Impact:** Gazecki is “manufacturing” a business failure to blame the Respondents, while failing his duty to mitigate losses.\n\n## 3. IDENTIFIED LITIGATION PATTERNS\n1. **Use of Law Firm as a Weapon:** Gazecki frequently sends aggressive commercial emails under his law firm letterhead (Legal Watch Australia) to intimidate suppliers.\n2. **Collateral Attacks:** Evidence suggests the current suit is a retaliatory strike against Joseph David Gauci, an informant in a separate Land and Environment Court contempt matter ([2025] NSWLEC 79).\n3. **Strategic Insolvency:** Moving assets or using family mortgages (e.g., Myall Rd farm) to appear “judgment proof” while maintaining a high-luxury lifestyle.\n\n## 4. UPCOMING HEARING GOALS (JUNE 5)\n- **Restore Security for Costs:** Prove Gazecki has access to third-party/family funds.\n- **Stay of Proceedings:** Argue “Abuse of Process” based on the @natasha.kovac social media comments and the JT email.\n- **Personal Liability:** Seek a Section 43 order to make Janek Gazecki personally liable for costs, bypassing the empty company shell.\n\n## 5. RELEVANT ENTITIES\n- **Polo Enterprises Holdings (PEA-1):** The “man of straw” applicant.\n- **Legal Watch Australia:** Gazecki’s law firm/letterhead.\n- **Events Queensland:** Licensing partner for the 2026 tour.\n- **Equi Ventures (JT):** Key supplier targeted for intimidation.\n"
  },
